---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Header from "../../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="EPA Sewer Grant | Who Is Abebe?">

  <Header>
    <Fragment slot="title">EPA Sewer Grant</Fragment>

    <Fragment slot="subtitle">
      A working file on EPA grant 03D02024, Waynesboro sewer improvements,
      field signage, and resident concerns.
    </Fragment>
  </Header>

  <main class="article-wrap">
    <article class="article-body report-page">

      <p class="lede">
        This report separates the EPA-funded sewer infrastructure work from the
        broader St. George Crossing report so the grant record, project signage,
        and resident concerns can be reviewed on their own.
      </p>

      <div class="notice-box">
        <strong>Scope:</strong>
        This page documents public grant information, a local field photo, and
        local reporting. It does not determine responsibility for any reported
        property damage or flooding.
      </div>

      <h2>EPA Grant Record</h2>

      <p>
        EPA grant record 03D02024 identifies funding connected to City of
        Waynesboro sewer improvement work, including sewer line replacement and
        upsizing.
      </p>

      <a
        class="document-row"
        href="https://enviro.epa.gov/envirofacts/nggs/report?grantId=03D02024"
        target="_blank"
      >
        <span>Federal Grant</span>
        <strong>EPA Grant 03D02024</strong>
        <p>EPA Envirofacts grant record for City of Waynesboro sewer improvements.</p>
      </a>

      <h2>Field Signage</h2>

      <p>
        The archive includes a local photo of the EPA project sign. This should
        be reviewed alongside the grant record and local reporting about sewer
        project impacts.
      </p>

      <figure class="report-figure">
        <img
          src="/docs/research/EPA-Macintosh.png"
          alt="EPA sewer project sign photo"
        />
        <figcaption>Local photo of EPA sewer project signage.</figcaption>
      </figure>

      <h2>Resident Concerns</h2>

      <p>
        The True Citizen article below reports resident concerns about the
        Waynesboro sewer project. It is included here because the reported issues
        should be compared against the EPA grant scope, project timeline, and
        field signage.
      </p>

      <a
        class="document-row"
        href="https://www.thetruecitizen.com/articles/waynesboro-residents-express-concerns-about-sewer-project/"
        target="_blank"
      >
        <span>Local Reporting</span>
        <strong>Waynesboro residents express concerns about sewer project</strong>
        <p>True Citizen article by Margaret Anne Brogan, published June 11, 2025.</p>
      </a>

      <h2>Working Notes</h2>

      <div class="fact-grid">
        <div class="fact-card">
          <span>Verified</span>
          <p>
            The archive includes an EPA grant link, a local EPA project sign
            photo, and a True Citizen article about resident concerns.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="fact-card">
          <span>Observation</span>
          <p>
            The sewer project appears in the same broader Waynesboro infrastructure
            context as development and housing-related records in the archive.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="fact-card">
          <span>Open Question</span>
          <p>
            More documentation is needed to compare the grant scope, contractor
            timeline, work completion, signage timing, and resident-reported impacts.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <a class="section-card" href="/reports/st-george-crossing">
        <span>Related Report</span>
        <h3>St. George Crossing</h3>
        <p>
          Review the broader Waynesboro development file and related municipal,
          property, and project materials.
        </p>
      </a>

    </article>
  </main>

  <Footer />

</BaseLayout>
